parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seatbelt can cause the seatbelt to jam or stick, making it difficult or impossible to secure the occupant in place, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The seatbelt is stuck in one position
the seatbelt will not retract or move
the seatbelt makes a clicking or grinding noise
the seatbelt is jammed at the top of the door
the seatbelt is stuck in an "L" shape

the motor has seized up.
